The paper proposes a modification to Q-learning, a popular reinforcement learning algorithm, by incorporating basic emotions to influence the agent's behavior. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The simulations conducted in the paper involve navigating through a maze, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of emotions to influence the agent's behavior has implications for human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
